name: BENE_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMBER ASSIGNED BY THE ENROLLMENT DATA BASE (EDB) TO EACH EDB RECORD TO IDENTIFY A BENEFICIARY.

name: BENE_TP_TYPE_CD
comment: THIS CODE IDENTIFIES WHETHER THE THIRD PARTY BUY-IN IS FOR PART A OR PART B.

name: BENE_RNG_BGN_DT
comment: THE PRIMARY BEGIN DATE FOR A BENEFICIARY DATE RANGE.

name: IDR_TRANS_EFCTV_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) IDENTIFYING WHEN A RECORD IS LOADED.

name: IDR_TRANS_OBSLT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN A RECORD WAS LAST KNOWN TO BE PRESENT IN THE SOURCE. THE CURRENT VERSION OF A RECORD WILL BE SET TO 12/31/9999 00:00:00.

name: IDR_LTST_TRANS_FLG
comment: AN INDICATOR ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) THAT IDENTIFIES WHICH TRANSACTION RECORD, BASED ON PRIMARY KEY, IS CONSIDERED TO REPRESENT THE MOST RECENT RECORD RECEIVED FROM THE SOURCE.    Y = LATEST VERSION OF THE RECORD  N = PREVIOUS VERSION OF THE RECORD

name: BENE_RNG_END_DT
comment: THE PRIMARY END DATE FOR A BENEFICIARY DATE RANGE.

name: BENE_TP_ACRTN_CD
comment: A CODE THAT INDICATES THE REASON FOR THE START PART A/PART B PREMIUM BILLING ACTION.

name: BENE_TP_ADJSTMT_CD
comment: BLANK OR Y SWITCH SET TO REQUIRE CURRENT MONTH BILLING.

name: BENE_TP_DLT_CD
comment: A CODE THAT INDICATES THE REASON FOR THE DELETION OF A BENEFICIARY FROM A THIRD PARTY PART A/PART B AGENCY.

name: BENE_TP_IDENT_CD
comment: AN ALPHA-NUMERIC CODE THAT IS USED TO ASSOCIATE AN ACTIVE THIRD PARTY PART A/PART B PERIOD WITH INACTIVE, PRIOR VERSIONS OF THE SAME PERIOD.

name: BENE_TP_IRMAA_AMT
comment: THE INCOME RELATED MONTHLY ADJUSTED AMOUNT (IRMAA) AMOUNT WHICH IS BEING BILLED OR HAS BEEN BILLED AS PART OF THE PART B PREMIUM FOR A PERIOD OF THIRD PARTY PART B COVERAGE.

name: BENE_TP_PNLTY_RATE_AMT
comment: THE PENALTY RATE FOR THE PART A/PART B THIRD PARTY PERIOD.

name: BENE_TP_PRCSG_BGN_DT
comment: THE MONTH THAT THE THIRD PARTY SYSTEM PROCESSED A THIRD PARTY AGENCYS PART A/PART B START BILLING ACTION.  ALSO KNOWN AS THE BILLING CYCLE DATE OR BILLING PERIOD FOR THIRD PARTY PREMIUMS.

name: BENE_TP_PRCSG_END_DT
comment: THE MONTH THAT THE THIRD PARTY SYSTEM PROCESSED A THIRD PARTY AGENCYS PART A/PART B STOP BILLING ACTION.

name: BENE_TP_PRM_PYR_CD
comment: A CODE THAT INDICATES WHETHER A MEDICARE BENEFICIARYS PREMIUMS ARE BEING PAID BY A THIRD PARTY. WHEN STATE BILLING IS INVOLVED, THE CODE INDICATES THAT THE BENEFICIARY IS DUALLY ELIGIBLE FOR MEDICARE AND MEDICAID.  THIS CODE IDENTIFIES MOST, BUT NOT ALL, PART B DUAL ELIGIBLE BENEFICIARIES. IF A STATE DOES NOT PAY PREMIUMS FOR CERTAIN ELIGIBILITY GROUPS (MEDICAL ASSISTANCE ONLY GROUPS, FOR EXAMPLE), THIS CODE WOULD NOT REFLECT A DUAL ELIGIBLE STATUS.  HOWEVER, THIS CODE IS MORE CURRENT AND MORE COMPLETE THAN MSIS DATA, SINCE NOT ALL STATES REPORT MSIS DATA.

name: BENE_TP_RDCD_PRM_AMT
comment: THE BENEFITS IMPROVEMENT AND PROTECTION ACT OF 2000 (BIPA) 606 PART B PREMIUM REDUCTION AMOUNT.

name: BENE_BUYIN_CD
comment: A CODE THAT INDICATES THE REASON FOR PART A/PART B STATE BUY-IN ELIGIBILITY.

name: BENE_VAR_PRM_CD
comment: VARIABLE PREMIUM INDICATOR.  INDICATES WHETHER THE PERIOD OF THIRD PARTY COVERAGE INVOLVES A VARIABLE PREMIUM RATE.

name: BENE_RDCD_PTA_PRM_SW
comment: A SWITCH THAT INDICATES IF A REDUCED PART A PREMIUM AMOUNT IS IN EFFECT.

name: META_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_LAST_UPDT_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS INSERTED.

name: META_LTST_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS SUBSEQUENTLY UPDATED.

name: IDR_INSRT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHILE PERFORMING AN INSERT OPERATION.

name: IDR_UPDT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN UPDATES ARE MADE TO ANY NON-PRIMARY KEY COLUMN.
